			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Well, I thought I posted this here, but maybe it got lost in another thread.
<br />

<br />
I recieved an email from Jim explaining why the number was set to 55%.
<br />

<br />
There is an inherent bonus of 25% on all spec line spells. So the 55% actually comes out to 68%. Now this, with the inherent 26% you can get from items and such, brings us to 94%. Only 2 levels of Avoidance of Magic and we hit 100% Immune!  <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile.gif" border="0" />
<br />

<br />
And yes, this 25% boost is across the board I am told. I have asked if maybe Sanya could put this into a future grab bag in more detail. So technically that level 20 Specline ROOT is actually a longer duration than listed, and more efficient and longer lasting than the baseline afterall. I would still prefer it to be AE, but it is INDEED a superior spell if you spec body and get it fairly early.
<br />

<br />
And again.... we are NOT Done with Sorceror changes. There are a few more coming soon, and they will impact RvR far more than PvE. <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile.gif" border="0" />
<br />

<br />
Now, I don't think it will help our survivablity much. Cause for all the nice stuff we are getting, it just makes people want to eliminate us that much faster. Hehe.... but thats a trade I am willing to take. I have never seen so many grey Sorcs in my life. I just hope a few of them play the class and get good at it like many of us here have, instead of being a pure PL'ed newb that does more harm than good to their groups.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
