			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Any skills, stats, hit points, power have a cap. I have 800+ SC and maxed out all I could on my outfit. Here are the caps at level 50 (These are less at lower levels)
<br />

<br />
Skills  -  +11 (Mind, Body, Etc)
<br />
Power -  +26 (Mana Pool)
<br />
Stats  -  +75 (Str, Con, Etc)
<br />
Hits    -  +200 (Health)
<br />
Resists- +26% (Energy, Matter, Etc)
<br />

<br />
You cannot getting anything higher then these with items, SC, etc. You can go higher with buffs for all of these except skills. Only way to get skills past +11 cap is with realm ranks. You get +1 for each realm rank you get and it goes to all skills. Also, each race starts off with a little built in resists. Sarcean, for instances, starts off with a base of 5% heat resist and 2% and 3% in some melee resists (Slash Crush, Thrust- not sure which ones) So, if he SC some armor to 26% resist to heat, he would have a total of 31% when wearing the outfit. To find out your base resists, just get naked! Just a FYI <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile.gif" border="0" />  
<br />

<br />
Kaz</span><span class="gensmall"><br /><br />Last edited by Kazaam ZzZzzZz on Sun Jan 26, 2003 1:57 pm, edited 1 time in total</span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
